The paper focuses on software development practices, specifically Continuous Integration (CI), which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of predictive models, which can be related to programming languages (cs.PL) and software development (cs.SD). Additionally, the paper analyzes data to find a balance between integrating often and keeping developers productive, which can be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
